  "children": [
    {
      "type": "prompt",
      "id": "HI8hy",
      "x": -756,
      "y": -70,
      "model": "claude-4.5-sonnet",
      "width": 483,
      "height": 4156,
      "content": "You are an expert Senior Frontend Engineer and portfolio designer. Create a production-ready GitHub Pages portfolio website for a Senior Frontend / Software Engineer with a frontend focus (React/Next.js ecosystem) that looks minimalist, premium, and credible.\n\nGoal\n\nBuild a clean, black-dominant, minimal portfolio for a senior frontend engineer. It must be fast, accessible, responsive, and easy to maintain. The site should help recruiters quickly understand skills, impact, and projects.\n\nConstraints\n\n• Design: minimalist, laconic, black-first theme (near-black background), subtle neutral borders, no heavy gradients, no “cosmic” background, no neon glow.\n• Tone: confident senior, concise, no fluff.\n• Performance: Lighthouse 95+ (Performance/Accessibility/Best Practices/SEO).\n• Accessibility: proper semantics, focus states, reduced motion support, good contrast.\n• Hosting: GitHub Pages (username.github.io), static output, no server needed.\n• Tech: choose a static-friendly stack (Astro or Vite). Avoid heavy runtime frameworks if not needed. Use plain HTML/CSS if that yields best performance. No external UI frameworks required.\n• Content language: English-only.\n• No tracking by default (no GA).\nInformation to include (use these as facts)\n\nRole/Positioning\n\n• Senior Frontend / Software Engineer\n• Focus: modern web apps, design systems, performance, UX, reliability\n• Interests: AI/ML applied to productivity and real products\nCore Skills\n\n• Frontend: TypeScript, JavaScript, React, Next.js (App Router), HTML, CSS, Tailwind CSS\n• UI/UX Engineering: component architecture, accessibility, responsive layout, micro-interactions (subtle), design systems\n• State/data: React Query, REST APIs\n• Backend-ish: Node.js, Prisma, PostgreSQL (basic to intermediate), API routes\n• Dev/Product: Git, CI basics, Vercel deployment, debugging, refactoring, code quality\n• Bonus: automation/agents tooling (OpenClaw), offline speech-to-text (Whisper / faster-whisper)\nProjects to showcase (create strong senior-style case studies even if details are light; focus on outcomes)\n\n1. “MyDiary” — personal diary / habit & health tracking web app  • Next.js, TypeScript, API routes, Prisma/Postgres, PWA (icons/versioning), Vercel deployment\n  • Features: TODO/day plans, editable cards, dedicated vacation checklist page, PWA cache/versioning\n\n2. “Roberto / OpenClaw automation” — personal assistant automation  • Offline voice transcription pipeline (Whisper/faster-whisper), Telegram commands, background jobs, productivity workflows\n\n3. GitHub Profile + GitHub Pages custom design  • Minimal design system, performance considerations, caching/versioned assets\n\nContacts (use placeholders, but structure the UI)\n\n• GitHub: https://github.com/<username>\n• Email: <email>\n• Telegram: https://t.me/<handle>\n• Optional: LinkedIn: <link>\nAdd a “Copy email” button.\nRequired pages/sections (single-page is fine)\n\n• Hero: name/title + 1–2 sentence value proposition + primary CTA (Email / GitHub)\n• About: short, senior, impact-focused\n• Skills: grouped, scannable (no long paragraphs)\n• Featured Projects: 3 cards with “role / stack / highlights / links”\n• Experience (optional): concise timeline (can be placeholder if unknown)\n• Open Source / Writing (optional)\n• Contact: clear links + copy-to-clipboard\nVisual system\n\n• Background: #0b0b0d or similar near-black\n• Surfaces: slightly lighter panels (e.g., rgba white 0.04–0.08)\n• Borders: subtle neutral (rgba white 0.10–0.16)\n• Typography: system font stack or Inter (optional, but optimize)\n• Buttons: minimal, high-contrast, consistent hover/focus\n• Avoid glassmorphism blur and avoid heavy shadows. If any shadow—very subtle.\nDeliverables\n\n1. Repository structure with all files.\n2. Full source code (HTML/CSS/JS or Astro/Vite).\n3. A README with:  • local dev instructions\n  • build & deploy to GitHub Pages\n  • how to edit content (skills/projects/links) in one place (e.g., content.json)\n\n4. Ensure:  • responsive layout\n  • accessible nav\n  • OpenGraph meta tags\n  • favicon placeholders\n  • SEO basics (title/description)\n  • print-friendly resume section optional\n\nImplementation details\n\n• Put all editable content into a single content.json (or .md if Astro).\n• Add a simple “theme token” system in CSS variables.\n• Add a small script for “copy email” and smooth scroll (respect reduced motion).\n• Use semantic HTML and avoid unnecessary JS.\nGenerate the complete solution now.\n"
    },
